


Appium Set up

1. Setting up Appium on MAC

	1. Install appium with node.js
	2. Install appium with with Appium Desktop Client
	3. Check installation & dependencies (appium-doctor)
	4. Uninstall appium

http://appium.io/

Step 1 : Check if node is installed on your system
    node -v

If node is not installed follow Step 2 and install it
Step 2 : Install node.js
    https://nodejs.org/en/download/
    https://brew.sh/
    brew install node

Step 3 : Check if node is installed
    node -v
    npm -v

Step 4 : Install appium
    npm install -g appium

Step 5 : Check appium is installed
    appium -v

Step 6 : Start appium
    appium


Installing appium with appium desktop client

Step 1 : Download appium desktop client - http://appium.io/
   https://github.com/appium/appium-desktop

Step 2 : Click on the .dmg file to install appium desktop client

Step 3 : Start appium desktop client

NOTE: if you get an error states "“Appium Server GUI” can’t be opened because Apple cannot check it for malicious software." Then, follow below:
-Go to System Preferences > Security & Privacy > General.
-Click on the "open anyway" button.
-Once it's done, try to open appium again.


2. Setting up Appium on WINDOWS

   	1. Install appium with node.js
   	2. Install appium with with Appium Desktop Client
   	3. Check installation & dependencies (appium-doctor)
   	4. Uninstall appium

Step 1 : Check if node is installed on your system
    node -v

If node is not installed follow Step 2 and install it
Step 2 : Install node.js
    https://nodejs.org/en/download/
    https://brew.sh/
    brew install node

Step 3 : Check if node is installed
    node -v
    npm -v

Step 4 : Install appium
    npm install -g appium

Step 5 : Check appium is installed
    appium -v

Step 6 : Start appium
    appium


Installing appium with appium desktop client

Step 1 : Download appium desktop client - http://appium.io/
   https://github.com/appium/appium-desktop

Step 2 : Click on the .exe file to install appium desktop client

Step 3 : Start appium desktop client



Appium-Doctor
-Appium doctor verifies that all dependencies required for starting the Appium server are there or not. If all green you have setup the Appium properly

https://www.npmjs.com/package/appium-doctor
https://github.com/appium/appium-doctor

npm install appium-doctor -g
MAC -> appium-doctor --ios
WINDOWS -> appium-doctor --android

HOW TO UNINSTALL APPIUM

If installed through node.js
npm uninstall -g appium

If installed Appium Desktop Client
Delete the app